	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>the way the magic/fire/cold etc and bane damages work is this:<br><br>IF it says magic 4, or bane undead 4.&nbsp;&nbsp;then it is calculated as if it was part of the weapons damage statistic. (damage x2, adds to damage bonus etc)<br><br>IF it says magic +4, or bane akhevan +4. Then the damage is added as a whole number to every blow.  It is not calculated into the weapon , nor is it subject to damage midigation.  the + damage type work just like procs. (generally think of them as rasing the minimum weapon damage)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
